    "Humans develop an intuitive understanding of how objects respond to forces since infancy (Wilkening and Cacchione, 2010; Ullman et al., 2017): a gentle poke causes a plant to sway, while a breeze creates rippling patterns across fabric.",
    "Do video generation models, which encode powerful visual and motion priors through internet-scale pretraining, possess a similar level of intuitive physics understanding?",
    "And if so, how to elicit their capabilities to interact with force inputs?",
    "A positive answer to these questions would provide a more flexible and expressive interface for video content creation, enable interactive video generation with user input (e.g., generating a video game), and eventually lead to an intuitive world model for intelligent agents to plan and make decisions with.",
